The Girl Scouts is one of the largest organizations for girls in the United States, with over 2.5 million youth members and over 800,000 adult members. The organization has a strong presence in many communities throughout the country, with over 50 million alumnae.
The Girl Scouts of the USA is a nonprofit organization that is funded through membership dues, donations, and grants. The organization is headquartered in New York City and has regional offices throughout the country.
The Girl Scouts of the USA offers a variety of programs for girls, including troop programs, camp programs, and service projects. The organization also offers leadership development programs and training for girls and adults.
The Girl Scouts of the USA is an important organization for girls in the United States. The organization provides girls with opportunities to develop their leadership skills, learn about community service, and have fun with their friends.

Black Panther is an American superhero film based on the Marvel Comics character of the same name. Produced by Marvel Studios and distributed by Walt Disney Studios Motion Pictures, it is the eighteenth film in the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU). The film is directed by Ryan Coogler, who co-wrote the screenplay with Joe Robert Cole, and stars Chadwick Boseman as T'Challa / Black Panther, alongside Michael B. Jordan, Lupita Nyong'o, Danai Gurira, Martin Freeman, Daniel Kaluuya, Letitia Wright, Winston Duke, Angela Bassett, Forest Whitaker, and Andy Serkis. In Black Panther, the Wakandans face a threat from the intergovernmental organization known as the International Security, Coordination, and Intelligence Agency (ISCI).
Black Panther is scheduled to be released in the United States on February 16, 2018, in IMAX and 3D.

2018年現在、メイン州の人口は1,338,404人です。
Maine is the northernmost state in the New England region of the United States. The state is bordered by New Hampshire to the west, the Atlantic Ocean to the southeast, and the Canadian provinces of Quebec to the northwest and New Brunswick to the northeast. Maine is the 12th-smallest by area, the 9th-least populous, and the 13th-least densely populated of the 50 U.S. states. It is known for its scenery—its jagged, mostly rocky coastline, its low, rolling mountains, its heavily forested interior, and its pond-dotted lakes and rivers. The western part of the state is closely tied to New Hampshire and Vermont as a cultural unit, and the state’s North Woods have given rise to a number of famous Maine woodsman, including Herb Clark, Molly Ockett, and Joseph “Joe” Polis, an Abenaki guide and trapper who was known for his skill in tracking and hunting.
The state is divided into 16 counties, which are further subdivided into 230 towns and plantations and 30 incorporated cities. The capital is Augusta. The largest city in the state is Portland, which has a population of 66,194 residents and a metro population of 523,698 residents. The largest metropolitan area in the state is the Portland-South Portland metropolitan area.
The state of Maine was part of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts until 1820, when it voted to secede from the newly formed United States of America. On March 15, 1820, it was admitted as the 23rd state under the Missouri Compromise. It was the last of the thirteen original colonies to join the Union.
Maine is a popular summer tourist destination, with more than 30 million visitors each year. Maine is the 38th most extensive, the 41st most populous, and the 43rd most densely populated of the 50 United States. Maine is the only state whose name has just one syllable.

The Lake Pontchartrain Causeway is the longest bridge in the United States that is not a suspension bridge. It is located in Louisiana and connects the city of New Orleans with the city of Slidell. The causeway is 24 miles (39 km) long and has a total length of 23,833 feet (7,253 m).
The Golden Gate Bridge is the longest suspension bridge in the United States. It is located in San Francisco, California and connects the city with Marin County. The bridge has a main span of 4,200 feet (1,280 m) and a total length of 8,981 feet (2,737 m).
The Mackinac Bridge is the longest suspension bridge in the United States that is not a suspension bridge. It is located in Michigan and connects the Lower Peninsula with the Upper Peninsula. The bridge has a main span of 3,800 feet (1,158 m) and a total length of 5,939 feet (1,811 m).
The George Washington Bridge is the longest suspension bridge in the United States that is not a suspension bridge. It is located in New York City and connects the boroughs of Manhattan and New Jersey. The bridge has a main span of 3,500 feet (1,067 m) and a total length of 4,760 feet (1,453 m).

Father's Day is a day of honor for fathers and celebrating fatherhood, paternal bonds, and the influence of fathers in society. Many countries celebrate it on the third Sunday of June, but it is also celebrated widely on other days. Father's Day was created to complement Mother's Day, a celebration that honors mothers and motherhood. Father's Day was founded in the United States in the early 20th century to complement Mother's Day in celebrating fatherhood and male parenting. Father's Day was founded in Spokane, Washington at the YMCA in 1910 by Sonora Smart Dodd, who was born in Arkansas. Its first celebration was in the Spokane YMCA on June 19, 1910. Her father, the Civil War veteran William Jackson Smart, was a single parent who raised his six children there.
